   135	# <a id="_Toc217286709"></a>2 Project Definition
   136	
   137	## <a id="_Toc217286710"></a>2\.01 Executive Summary
   138	
   139	Pivot Interiors is implementing NetSuite Orion to modernize its commission management operations and replace manual processes currently managed through Microsoft Dynamics 365 and Excel spreadsheets\. This Business Requirements Document \(BRD\) captures the business requirements discovered during the Commission Management process mapping phase\.
   140	
   141	Through the CRM\-Commissions discovery session conducted on __August 25, 2025, and subsequent meetings__, GSI analyzed Pivot's current state commission processes across multiple sales roles including Account Managers, New Business Development Executives, Customer Success Managers, Key Account Managers, and Construction Solutions Sales Representatives\.
   142	
   143	<a id="_Toc217286711"></a>__2\.02 Company Overview__
   144	
   145	Pivot Interiors, Inc\. is a leading California\-based design firm recognized for its team of innovators, creators, and thought leaders who specialize in delivering exceptional interior solutions for businesses of all sizes\. Their work captures the essence of each client’s brand while fostering environments that inspire employees to thrive, create, and collaborate\. Headquartered in the Bay Area, Pivot Interiors operates offices and Design Centers across the state, including Santa Clara, Fremont, San Francisco, Costa Mesa, Los Angeles, and La Mirada\. As a MillerKnoll Certified Dealer, Pivot Interiors invites clients to experience its uniquely crafted spaces and the distinctive quality that defines the Pivot Interiors brand\.
   146	
   147	[__https://www\.pivotinteriors\.com__](https://www.pivotinteriors.com)
   148	
   149	<a id="_Toc217286712"></a>__2\.03 NetSuite Orion Overview__
   150	
   151	The NetSuite Orion Commissions Module is a sophisticated sales commission management system designed to automate the calculation, tracking, and payment of sales commissions\.
   152	
   153	<a id="_Toc217286713"></a>__2\.04 Project Overview__
   154	
   155	Pivot’s current engagement with GSI is based around the creation and implementation of a set of business requirements appropriate to its business operations both today and scaling into the future\. This project primarily consists of the following stages:
   156	
   157	- __Discover__: Evaluate the dealer’s business processes with NetSuite Orion capabilities
   158	- __Realize__: Perform initial setup, installation and configuration of your NetSuite instance
   159	- __Educate__: Empower your team for success through comprehensive training and user adoption support
   160	- __Actualize__: Bring your NetSuite and Orion solution to life with seamless data migration and go\-live support
   161	- __Maximize__: Support and expand your operations with dedicated ongoing assistance and strategic customizations\.
   162	
   163	Our implementation approach is “Align, Adapt, Accommodate”\.
   164	
   165	- Align – Existing processes fit in NetSuite Orion as is\.
   166	- Adapt – Pivot will change its processes to fit in NetSuite Orion as is\.
   167	- Accommodate – GSI will create a configuration specific to Pivot Interiors, or if the feature can benefit others, will update the code base to make the feature standard\.
   168	
   169	<a id="_Toc217286714"></a>__2\.05 Document Objectives__
   170	
   171	The purpose of this document is to summarize functional and procedural requirements captured by GSI during the Discover business process mapping phase of the implementation\. 
   172	
   173	This Business Requirements Document \(BRD\) documents your goals, the problems you want to solve, and the outcomes you expect\. It is the foundation for the setting up of the system, acting as a __roadmap between your business needs and the solution design__\.
   174	
   175	This document represents information gathered in meetings held with the Client, which enables the GSI team to map the business requirements to an efficient flow in the NetSuite Orion application\. Once complete, this document will serve as a blueprint for the GSI team to configure the application\. This document does not supersede the Statement of Work\. The Statement of Work determines scope\. 
   176	
   177	A series of process mapping discovery sessions, focusing on the key areas of the business, were used as a starting point for this exercise\. This document remains consistent in structure to those discovery sessions as it categorizes the findings into the same key process areas\. The set of business requirements documentation is inclusive of all business requirements provided by the Client\.
   178	
   179	# <a id="_Toc217286715"></a>3 Commission Management
   180	
   181	## <a id="_Toc217286716"></a>3\.01 Commission Plan Configuration
   182	
   183	3\.01\.01 Your Business Requirements
   184	
   185	- REQ\-3\.01\.01: Support cumulative annual commission calculations based on calendar year
   186	- REQ\-3\.01\.02: Commission calculations triggered by invoice date
   187	- REQ\-3\.01\.03: Support multiple commission plan types across different sales roles
   188	- REQ\-3\.01\.04: Commission plans stored with complex calculation rules via JSON configurations
   189	- REQ\-3\.01\.05: Support date\-based validity for commission plans with fiscal year alignment
   190	
   191	3\.01\.02 Current State Process
   192	
   193	Pivot currently manages multiple compensation plans across different sales roles\. The current commission plans are based on cumulative annual calculations tied to calendar year and invoice date\.
   194	
   195	__Current State Challenges__:
   196	
   197	- Manual calculation processes prone to errors
   198	- Multiple Excel spreadsheets for tracking
   199	- Time\-consuming reconciliation at year\-end
   200	- Difficulty tracking cumulative YTD progress
   201	- Limited visibility for sales representatives
   202	
   203	User Story:
   204	
   205	- As a Commission Administrator, I need automated cumulative annual commission calculations so that we can eliminate manual tracking and ensure accurate, timely commission payments\.
   206	
   207	3\.01\.03 NetSuite Orion Solution
   208	
   209	NetSuite Orion's Commission Module will be configured to support Pivot's cumulative annual calculation methodology\. As decided during discovery: "We will build cumulative annual functionality into the Orion module to support the existing commission structure\. Calendar year and based on invoice date\."
   210	
   211	3\.01\.04 Future State Process
   212	
   213	1. __Plan Assignment:__ Commission plans assigned to sales representatives based on role
   214	2. __Transaction Processing:__ Invoices trigger commission calculation upon posting
   215	3. __Cumulative Tracking:__ System maintains YTD cumulative Invoiced GP totals automatically
   216	4. __Tier Evaluation:__ Appropriate commission rate applied based on cumulative thresholds
   217	5. __Calculation Generation:__ Commission calculation records created with full audit trail
   218	6. __Approval Workflow:__ Calculations route for review and approval
   219	7. __Payment Processing:__ Approved calculations consolidated for payment
