Financial Management/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_FinancialManagement_v2.0.md:893:KB+Hoag's current commission structure includes a 15% contingency markup on labor costs. This markup:
Financial Management/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_FinancialManagement_v2.0.md:894:- Adds 15% to labor line items before calculating commissions
Financial Management/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_FinancialManagement_v2.0.md:895:- Affects commission calculations (commission is paid on the markup as well as base labor)
Financial Management/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_FinancialManagement_v2.0.md:896:- Creates a difference between Project GP (actual cost-based) and Commissionable GP (cost + markup)
Financial Management/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_FinancialManagement_v2.0.md:898:Sales teams see Commissionable GP (which includes the 15% markup) for commission purposes. Management sees true Project GP (without markup) for actual profitability analysis.
Financial Management/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_FinancialManagement_v2.0.md:902:Orion/NetSuite enables both approaches through flexible project accounting and reporting capabilities:
Financial Management/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_FinancialManagement_v2.0.md:905:If leadership decides to continue the 15% markup, custom script development can automate the calculation at order line-item level. The markup would be calculated and added to labor costs automatically. Commission rules would be configured to apply commissions to the total (base labor + markup). Project GP and Commissionable GP would be tracked separately through distinct custom fields and calculated values.
Financial Management/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_FinancialManagement_v2.0.md:908:If leadership decides to eliminate the markup, all labor costs would be charged at actual cost. Commissions would be based on actual project costs only. Project GP and Commissionable GP would converge (or the distinction could be eliminated entirely). Sales team would need clear communication about the impact on commission calculations.
Financial Management/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_FinancialManagement_v2.0.md:915:At order line-item entry, labor costs are entered. The system automatically calculates and applies the 15% markup, creating a total labor line value. Commission calculations apply commissions to this total (base + markup). At project completion, the system generates two reporting views: Project GP (actual cost) and Commissionable GP (cost + markup). Sales teams access dashboards showing Commissionable GP. Management accesses dashboards showing true Project GP for actual profitability analysis.
Financial Management/KBMH/3 Output/BRD_FinancialManagement_v2.0.md:918:At order line-item entry, labor costs are entered at actual value. No markup is automatically applied. Commission calculations apply commissions to actual costs only. Project GP reflects true profitability without any contingency markup. This requires change communication to sales teams about commission impacts.
